    {
        "content": "<p>I changed the topic title to better reflect the topic at hand.</p>\n<p>Also, just as there is a 2-functor,</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mo>−</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">p</mi></mrow><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">[-,\\mathrm{Set}]: \\mathrm{Cat} \\to \\mathfrak{BTop} ,</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Cat</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.88585em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathfrak\">BTop</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>taking categories to their category of (co)presheaves, does it also hold there is an analogous 2-functor,</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mo>−</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mtext>pointed</mtext></msub><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">p</mi></mrow><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">[-,\\mathrm{Set}]: \\mathrm{Cat}|_\\text{pointed} \\to\\mathrm{Set}/\\mathfrak{BTop},</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.036108em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Cat</span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord text mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">pointed</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathfrak\">BTop</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>taking pointed categories to their category of \"pointed\" (co)presheaves?</p>",
        "id": 249438143,
        "sender_full_name": "Keith Peterson",
        "timestamp": 1628912286
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"389450\">Keith Peterson</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/230087-theory.3A-topos.20theory/topic/A.202-category.20of.20pointed.20toposes.3F/near/249333704\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275920\">John Baez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/230087-theory.3A-topos.20theory/topic/A.20category.20of.20pointed.20toposes.3F/near/249306167\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I thought an object of this 2-category was a topos <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> equipped with a \"point\", meaning a geometric morphism <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to \\mathrm{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/point+of+a+topos\">The nlab</a> gives points in toposes in the opposite direction.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Okay, you're right.</p>",
        "id": 249439434,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628913974
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A geometric morphism is a pair of adjoint functors, with the left adjoint also preserving finite limits.</p>",
        "id": 249439544,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628914177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, it has arrows going both ways.   One is primary if you're doing geometry, the other is primary if you're doing algebra.</p>",
        "id": 249439634,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628914243
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The \"official\" direction is the geometric direction, which is the direction of the left adjoint.   The category Set is the category of sheaves on a point.  So, a \"point\" of a topos <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is a geometric morphism where the left adjoint goes like <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathrm{Set} \\to X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 249439703,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628914412
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I tend to like the algebraic direction: for example, a model of a Lawvere theory <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is a product-preserving functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to \\mathrm{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span></span></span></span>, and similarly we can think of a point of a topos <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> as a model of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> in the category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span></span></span></span>.... but it's the <em>right adjoint</em> part of geometric morphism that's a functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to \\mathrm{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 249439881,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628914631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, I tend to slip up and use the opposite of the \"official\" direction when thinking about geometric morphisms.</p>",
        "id": 249439922,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628914694
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anyway, my <em>point</em> (pardon the pun) was that there's no subtlety in defining the objects of the category of pointed toposes: you already know what a pointed topos is.</p>",
        "id": 249440039,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1628914873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"389450\">@Keith Peterson</span> Yes.  In general, any (2-)functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F:C\\to D</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span></span></span></span> induces a functor on coslice categories <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>c</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">c/F : c/C \\to F(c)/D</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 249443013,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1628919818
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275920\">John Baez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/230087-theory.3A-topos.20theory/topic/A.202-category.20of.20pointed.20toposes.3F/near/249439703\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The \"official\" direction is the geometric direction, which is the direction of the left adjoint.   The category Set is the category of sheaves on a point.  So, a \"point\" of a topos <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is a geometric morphism where the left adjoint goes like <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathrm{Set} \\to X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The geometric direction is that of the right adjoint...</p>",
        "id": 249443497,
        "sender_full_name": "David Michael Roberts",
        "timestamp": 1628920697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And the rest of what you said needs the left and right swapped :-/</p>",
        "id": 249443514,
        "sender_full_name": "David Michael Roberts",
        "timestamp": 1628920747
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"275920\">@John Baez</span> sounds like you've got the directions mixed up!</p>",
